msgid "step_1"
msgstr "On the receiver domain, create a user with administrator rights in the WordPress dashboard under “Users”, for example “api_elabel”, or use an existing administrator."

msgid "step_2"
msgstr "Open “Edit User” and create an application password in the user profile. The name of the application password can be chosen freely, for example “api_elabel”. Then generate it, copy it and store it safely."

msgid "step_3"
msgstr "Enter the receiver URL, the username and the application password in the main plugin."

msgid "step_4"
msgstr "In the main plugin, test whether the connection to the receiver instance works. Also verify that the REST API is reachable and not blocked by a firewall, a security plugin or an auth redirect."

msgid "step_5"
msgstr "The main plugin will then send the E-labels to this receiver instance and create an E-label page there."

msgid "step_6"
msgstr "Test the transfer with a sample product and verify that the E-label page was created correctly on the receiver site and can be opened."

